{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/CoordinateSystems"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"AstronomyKit"}],"title":"Coordinate Systems","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Position Calculations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/CelestialPositions","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/CelestialBody","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Observer","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Constellation","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Aberration","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/EquatorDate"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Position-Calculations"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"AstronomyKit supports multiple coordinate systems and provides rotation matrices for transforming between them. Understanding these systems is essential for precise astronomical work.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Coordinate Systems","anchor":"Coordinate-Systems","level":2},{"type":"heading","text":"Equatorial J2000 (EQJ)","anchor":"Equatorial-J2000-EQJ","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The standard reference frame used by most star catalogs:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Origin: Earth’s center","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fundamental plane: Earth’s equator at J2000.0 epoch"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Primary direction: Vernal equinox at J2000.0"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let eq = try CelestialBody.mars.equatorial(at: .now, equatorDate: .j2000)","print(\"RA: \\(eq.rightAscension)h, Dec: \\(eq.declination)°\")"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Equatorial of Date (EQD)","anchor":"Equatorial-of-Date-EQD","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Accounts for precession of Earth’s axis:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Same as EQJ but referenced to the current date"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let eq = try CelestialBody.mars.equatorial(at: .now, equatorDate: .ofDate)"]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Ecliptic (ECL)","anchor":"Ecliptic-ECL"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Referenced to the plane of Earth’s orbit:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Fundamental plane: Ecliptic (Earth’s orbital plane)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Primary direction: Vernal equinox","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let lon = try CelestialBody.jupiter.eclipticLongitude(at: .now)","print(\"Ecliptic longitude: \\(lon)°\")","","\/\/ Full ecliptic position","let sunPos = try Sun.position(at: .now)","print(\"λ: \\(sunPos.longitude)°, β: \\(sunPos.latitude)°\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Horizontal (HOR)","anchor":"Horizontal-HOR"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Local sky coordinates for an observer:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Altitude: Height above the horizon"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Azimuth: Compass direction from north"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let observer = Observer(latitude: 40.0, longitude: -74.0)","let hor = try CelestialBody.venus.horizon(at: .now, from: observer)","print(\"Alt: \\(hor.altitude)°, Az: \\(hor.azimuth)°\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Galactic (GAL)","anchor":"Galactic-GAL"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Referenced to the Milky Way:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fundamental plane: Galactic plane"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Primary direction: Galactic center"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Available via rotation matrices (see below).","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Rotation Matrices","anchor":"Rotation-Matrices"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Creating Rotation Matrices","anchor":"Creating-Rotation-Matrices"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Equatorial J2000 to Ecliptic","let eqjToEcl = try RotationMatrix.equatorialJ2000ToEcliptic()","","\/\/ Ecliptic to Equatorial J2000","let eclToEqj = try RotationMatrix.eclipticToEquatorialJ2000()","","\/\/ Equatorial J2000 to Galactic","let eqjToGal = try RotationMatrix.equatorialJ2000ToGalactic()"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Time-Dependent Rotations","anchor":"Time-Dependent-Rotations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some transformations require a time for precession\/nutation:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Equatorial J2000 to Equatorial of Date","let time = AstroTime.now","let eqjToEqd = try RotationMatrix.equatorialJ2000ToEquatorialOfDate(at: time)","","\/\/ Equatorial to Horizontal (requires time and observer)","let observer = Observer.greenwich","let eqjToHor = try RotationMatrix.equatorialJ2000ToHorizon(at: time, from: observer)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Applying Rotations","anchor":"Applying-Rotations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Transform a vector using a rotation matrix:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let position = try CelestialBody.mars.geocentricPosition(at: .now)","let rotation = try RotationMatrix.equatorialJ2000ToEcliptic()","let eclipticPosition = position.rotated(by: rotation)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Matrix Operations","anchor":"Matrix-Operations"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Identity (no rotation)","let identity = RotationMatrix.identity","","\/\/ Inverse (reverse rotation)","let forward = try RotationMatrix.equatorialJ2000ToEcliptic()","let reverse = forward.inverse","","\/\/ Combine rotations","let combined = try forward.combined(with: anotherRotation)","","\/\/ Pivot around an axis","let rotated = try RotationMatrix.pivot(axis: 2, angle: 45.0)  \/\/ 45° around Z"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Vector Types","anchor":"Vector-Types"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Vector3D","anchor":"Vector3D"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A 3D Cartesian position vector:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let pos = try CelestialBody.jupiter.geocentricPosition(at: .now)","print(\"X: \\(pos.x) AU\")","print(\"Y: \\(pos.y) AU\")","print(\"Z: \\(pos.z) AU\")","print(\"Magnitude: \\(pos.magnitude) AU\")","","\/\/ Normalize to unit vector","let direction = pos.normalized"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"StateVector","anchor":"StateVector"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Position and velocity together:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let state = try observer.state(at: .now)","print(\"Position: \\(state.position)\")","print(\"Velocity: \\(state.velocity)\")  \/\/ AU\/day"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Spherical Coordinates","anchor":"Spherical-Coordinates"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Used for Moon’s ecliptic position:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let moonPos = try Moon.eclipticPosition(at: .now)","print(\"Longitude: \\(moonPos.longitude)°\")","print(\"Latitude: \\(moonPos.latitude)°\")","print(\"Distance: \\(moonPos.distance) AU\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Atmospheric Effects","anchor":"Atmospheric-Effects"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Refraction","anchor":"Refraction"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Atmospheric refraction bends light, affecting apparent altitude:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Normal refraction correction (default)","let apparent = try body.horizon(at: .now, from: observer, refraction: .normal)","","\/\/ No refraction (geometric position)","let geometric = try body.horizon(at: .now, from: observer, refraction: .none)","","\/\/ JPL Horizons refraction model","let jpl = try body.horizon(at: .now, from: observer, refraction: .jplHorizons)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Computing Refraction Directly","anchor":"Computing-Refraction-Directly"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calculate refraction angles independently of a coordinate conversion:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ How much does refraction raise an object at 5° geometric altitude?","let offset = Refraction.normal.refractionAngle(at: 5.0)","print(\"Refraction at 5°: +\\(offset)°\")","","\/\/ Given an apparent altitude of 5°, what was the geometric altitude?","let inverse = Refraction.normal.inverseRefractionAngle(at: 5.0)","let geometric = 5.0 - inverse"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Aberration","anchor":"Aberration"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Light-time and stellar aberration affect apparent positions:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ With aberration correction (default) - what you actually see","let apparent = try body.geocentricPosition(at: .now, aberration: .corrected)","","\/\/ Without correction - geometric position","let geometric = try body.geocentricPosition(at: .now, aberration: .none)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Available Rotations","anchor":"Avai